The `Shuffle` function takes in a `List` where `T` can be any type of object, and shuffles the elements randomly using the Fisher-Yates algorithm.

Certainly! Here's a MATLAB code that recursively calculates the size of a directory and its subdirectories:
```
function [totalSize] = getDirectorySize(dirPath)
% This function recursively calculates the size of a directory and its subdirectories
% Input: dirPath - the path to the directory
% Output: totalSize - the total size of the directory and its subdirectories (in bytes)
% Get the directory listing
dirList = dir(dirPath);
% Initialize the total size to zero
totalSize = 0;
% Loop through the directory listing
for i = 1:length(dirList)
 % Check if the current item is a directory
 if dirList(i).isdir && ~strcmp(dirList(i).name,'.') && ~strcmp(dirList(i).name,'..')
 % If it is a directory, recursively call this function on the subdirectory
 subDirPath = fullfile(dirPath, dirList(i).name);
 totalSize = totalSize + getDirectorySize(subDirPath);
 else
 % If it is a file, add its size to the total size
 totalSize = totalSize + dirList(i).bytes;
 end
end
```
To use this function, simply call it with the path to the directory you want to calculate the size of:
```
dirPath = 'C:pathtodirectory';
totalSize = getDirectorySize(dirPath);
```
This will return the total size of the directory and its subdirectories in bytes.

Yes, you can modify the function to convert the byte size to a more human-readable format. Here's an updated version of the MATLAB code that converts the total size to megabytes (MB) and gigabytes (GB):
```
function [totalSizeStr] = getDirectorySize(dirPath)
% This function recursively calculates the size of a directory and its subdirectories
% Input: dirPath - the path to the directory
% Output: totalSizeStr - the total size of the directory and its subdirectories (in a human-readable format)
% Get the directory listing
dirList = dir(dirPath);
% Initialize the total size to zero
totalSize = 0;
% Loop through the directory listing
for i = 1:length(dirList)
 % Check if the current item is a directory
 if dirList(i).isdir && ~strcmp(dirList(i).name,'.') && ~strcmp(dirList(i).name,'..')
 % If it is a directory, recursively call this function on the subdirectory
 subDirPath = fullfile(dirPath, dirList(i).name);
 totalSize = totalSize + getDirectorySize(subDirPath);
 else
 % If it is a file, add its size to the total size
 totalSize = totalSize + dirList(i).bytes;
 end
end

% Convert the total size to MB and GB
if totalSize < 2^20 % less than 1MB
 totalSizeStr = sprintf('%.2f bytes', totalSize);
elseif totalSize < 2^30 % less than 1GB
 totalSizeStr = sprintf('%.2f MB', totalSize/2^20);
else % 1GB or more
 totalSizeStr = sprintf('%.2f GB', totalSize/2^30);
end
```
This updated function returns the total size in a string format that is more readable, such as "56.78 MB" or "2.34 GB".

